content.text:
I now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire relevant codebase. Let me formulate the detailed implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: Unified Dashboard Section ("Morning Briefing")

### 1. Overview and Architecture

The goal is to combine `WeeklyRecapCard` and `DailyPromptCard` into a single cohesive `DashboardBriefing` component that sits at the top of the PostCards feed. This new component acts as a visual container wrapper that embeds refactored versions of the existing cards as sub-sections, preserving all functionality while creating visual unity.

**New files to create:**
- `client/src/components/DashboardBriefing/DashboardBriefing.jsx` -- wrapper/orchestrator component
- `client/src/components/DashboardBriefing/DashboardBriefing.css` -- all dashboard-specific styles
- `client/src/components/DashboardBriefing/RecapSection.jsx` -- refactored recap content (extracted from WeeklyRecapCard)
- `client/src/components/DashboardBriefing/PromptSection.jsx` -- refactored prompt content (extracted from DailyPromptCard)

**Files to modify:**
- `client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/PostCards.jsx` -- replace the two separate card renders with a single `<DashboardBriefing />` render

**Files to leave untouched (but imported from):**
- `client/API/Api.js` -- no changes needed, existing API functions are reused
- `client/src/components/Streak/useStreakData.js` -- reused to optionally show streak in dashboard
- Existing `WeeklyRecapCard.jsx`, `DailyPromptCard.jsx`, and their CSS files -- can be left in place for backward compatibility but are no longer rendered in PostCards

### 2. Component Architecture

```
DashboardBriefing (wrapper)
  |
  |-- Dashboard header ("Today" label + date + optional streak badge + dismiss button)
  |
  |-- CSS Grid container
  |     |
  |     |-- RecapSection (left on desktop / top on mobile)
  |     |     |-- Stat chips row (posts, words, reactions, views)
  |     |     |-- Expandable detail area (best post, community, most active, most reacted)
  |     |
  |     |-- Visual divider (vertical line on desktop, horizontal on mobile)
  |     |
  |     |-- PromptSection (right on desktop / bottom on mobile)
  |           |-- Category pill
  |           |-- Prompt text
  |           |-- "Write your take" button + response avatars
  |
  |-- Framer Motion AnimatePresence (for dismiss animation)
```

**DashboardBriefing.jsx** -- The orchestrator:
- Manages the `dismissed` state (localStorage-backed, keyed by week like the current WeeklyRecapCard)
- Fetches both data sources via React Query hooks (recap + prompt + optionally streak)
- Renders nothing if both data sources are empty/loading AND the user is not logged in
- Passes `onDismiss` callback and data props down to sub-sections
- The key insight: the entire dashboard dismisses as a unit (one dismiss button), not each section individually. When the user dismisses the recap, the whole dashboard goes away for the week. The prompt section is always visible even without recap data (as a standalone), but when recap IS available, they form a unified card.

Actually, looking more carefully at the requirements and current behavior, I want to refine this. Currently:
- WeeklyRecapCard has its own dismiss (localStorage per week, returns null when dismissed)
- DailyPromptCard has no dismiss; it shows whenever there is a prompt

The dashboard should preserve this behavior. The dismiss button should only dismiss the recap portion. If the recap is dismissed or has no data, the dashboard should gracefully degrade: it becomes just the prompt section (still inside the dashboard wrapper, maintaining visual consistency). If there is no prompt AND no recap, the entire dashboard renders nothing.

### 3. Layout Strategy

**Desktop (above 480px):** CSS Grid with two columns.

```css
.dashboard-briefing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1.2fr;  /* recap | divider | prompt */
    gap: 0;
    align-items: start;
}
```

The `1fr` / `1.2fr` ratio gives the prompt section slightly more horizontal space since it contains longer text content. The `auto` column is a thin vertical divider.

When recap is dismissed or absent, the grid collapses to a single column:
```css
.dashboard-briefing-grid.prompt-only {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
}
```

**Mobile (480px and below):** Single column stack.
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
    .dashboard-briefing-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
}
```

The divider rotates from vertical to horizontal on mobile.

### 4. Visual Design Details

**Outer container (`.dashboard-briefing`):**
```css
.dashboard-briefing {
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-card);
    border-radius: 14px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card-sm);
}
```

This uses `--bg-card` (white/near-white in light mode, `#161614` in dark) rather than a flashy gradient. The existing cards use different bg approaches (gradient for recap, `--card-bg` for prompt). A single clean card bg with internal visual differentiation is more cohesive.

**Dashboard header (`.dashboard-briefing-header`):**
```css
.dashboard-briefing-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 14px 20px 0 20px;
}
```

The header contains:
- A small amber/gold accent line (2px thick, ~20px wide) as a decorative element -- mimicking the editorial "pull quote" feel
- "Today" in `font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-heading);` -- using the editorial heading font at a small scale gives it a refined newspaper feel
- The current date formatted as "Wed, Feb 26" in `font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-faint); letter-spacing: 0.3px;`
- Optional StreakBadge (pulled from `useStreakData`) to the right of the date
- Dismiss button (X) on far right (only visible when recap data exists)

**Accent treatment:** Instead of the gradient background that the recap currently uses, use a subtle left-border accent on the entire card:
```css
.dashboard-briefing {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-amber);
}
```

This is a common editorial pattern -- a gold left-border on a clean white card -- that creates immediate visual distinction without being heavy-handed.

**Recap section (`.dashboard-recap-section`):**
```css
.dashboard-recap-section {
    padding: 12px 20px 14px 20px;
}
```

The stat chips should be displayed as a horizontal row using a compact inline format:
```css
.dashboard-stat-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.dashboard-stat {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 4px;
}

.dashboard-stat-value {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    line-height: 1;
}

.dashboard-stat-label {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: lowercase;
}
```

This is more compact than the current vertical stat layout. The stats read as "3 posts  1.2K words  8 reactions  42 views" on a single line. The dividers between stats are removed; the gap alone provides separation. Clicking this row still toggles the expanded details.

The expand chevron goes at the far right of the stat row, same as current behavior.

**Vertical divider (desktop only):**
```css
.dashboard-divider {
    width: 1px;
    align-self: stretch;
    background: var(--border-card);
    margin: 12px 0;
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
    .dashboard-divider {
        width: 100%;
        height: 1px;
        margin: 0 20px;
        align-self: center;
    }
}
```

**Prompt section (`.dashboard-prompt-section`):**
```css
.dashboard-prompt-section {
    padding: 12px 20px 14px 20px;
}
```

Internal layout is largely preserved from the current DailyPromptCard:
- Sub-header: bulb icon + "Today's Prompt" label + category pill (same as current, just without its own card wrapper)
- Prompt text: `font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--text-heading);` -- using the serif font (Lora) at a moderate size creates the "editorial briefing" feel
- Footer: "Write your take" button + response avatars (preserved as-is)

**Typography choices (from existing design system):**
- Dashboard header "Today": `'Playfair Display', serif` at 15px, weight 600
- Stat values: `var(--font-ui)` (Outfit) at 18px, weight 700
- Stat labels: `var(--font-ui)` (Outfit) at 11px, weight 500
- Prompt text: `var(--font-serif)` (Lora) at 15px, weight 500
- Section sub-labels ("Your Week", "Today's Prompt"): `var(--font-ui)` at 11px, weight 600, uppercase, `letter-spacing: 0.4px`
- All accent colors: `var(--accent-amber)` / `#D4A853` (existing system)

**Color palette (all from existing CSS variables):**
- Card bg: `var(--bg-card)`
- Border: `var(--border-card)` with left accent `var(--accent-amber)`
- Text: `var(--text-heading)`, `var(--text-secondary)`, `var(--text-muted)`, `var(--text-faint)`
- Accent: `var(--accent-amber)` for the left border, button hover, and icon colors
- All theme-aware (light + dark mode work automatically through CSS variables)

### 5. How Existing Functionality Is Preserved

| Feature | Current | New |
|---|---|---|
| Recap dismiss (localStorage per week key) | `WeeklyRecapCard` manages internally | `DashboardBriefing` manages the recap dismissed state using the same `getWeekKey()` function and localStorage pattern |
| Recap expand/collapse details | `expanded` state + AnimatePresence in WeeklyRecapCard | `RecapSection` manages its own `expanded` state identically |
| Prompt "Write your take" callback | `onWriteResponse` prop from PostCards | `DashboardBriefing` receives `onWriteResponse` prop, passes through to `PromptSection` |
| Prompt response avatars + count | React Query fetch in DailyPromptCard | `PromptSection` uses same `useQuery` hooks |
| Recap data fetch | React Query in WeeklyRecapCard | `DashboardBriefing` or `RecapSection` uses same `useQuery` with same keys |
| Visibility: only when logged in and not searching | `{!isSearchMode && session && (...)}` wrapping each card | Same conditional wraps `<DashboardBriefing />` in PostCards |
| Recap: show nothing when no data or dismissed | `return null` conditions in WeeklyRecapCard | `RecapSection` returns null, parent grid adapts to single-column |
| Prompt: show nothing when no prompt | `return null` in DailyPromptCard | `PromptSection` returns null, parent handles |

### 6. Animation/Motion Strategy

**Entry animation (whole dashboard):**
```jsx
<motion.div
    className="dashboard-briefing"
    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: -10 }}
    animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.35, ease: 'easeOut' }}
>
```

Subtle slide-down + fade. Matches the current WeeklyRecapCard's `y: -12` entry but slightly less dramatic since the dashboard is bigger.

**Recap dismiss animation:**
When recap is dismissed, only the recap section collapses. The grid animates from two-column to single-column:
```jsx
<AnimatePresence mode="popLayout">
    {showRecap && (
        <motion.div
            className="dashboard-recap-section"
            key="recap"
            initial={{ opacity: 1, width: 'auto' }}
            exit={{ opacity: 0, width: 0, padding: 0, overflow: 'hidden' }}
            transition={{ duration: 0.3, ease: 'easeInOut' }}
        >
            <RecapSection ... />
        </motion.div>
    )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

On mobile, the exit is vertical (height collapse) instead of width collapse.

**Recap expand animation:**
Same as current -- `motion.div` with `height: 0` to `height: 'auto'` + opacity fade. Preserved exactly from the existing code.

**Full dashboard exit (if both sections become null):**
```jsx
<AnimatePresence>
    {showDashboard && (
        <motion.div exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -15, transition: { duration: 0.25 } }}>
            ...
        </motion.div>
    )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

### 7. Detailed Implementation Steps

**Step 1: Create `DashboardBriefing.jsx`**

```
client/src/components/DashboardBriefing/DashboardBriefing.jsx
```

This component:
- Imports `useQuery` from `@tanstack/react-query`
- Imports `motion, AnimatePresence` from `framer-motion`
- Imports `useAuth` for session/user
- Imports `getWeeklyRecap, getTodaysPrompt, getPromptResponses` from API
- Imports `useStreakData` for optional streak badge display
- Imports `RecapSection` and `PromptSection`
- Manages recap dismiss state (extract `getWeekKey` as a shared util or inline)
- Receives `onWriteResponse` prop (passed through from PostCards)
- Determines `showRecap` and `showPrompt` booleans
- If neither, returns null
- Renders the outer `motion.div` with the dashboard container, header, grid, and sub-sections

Key code structure:
```jsx
const DashboardBriefing = ({ onWriteResponse }) => {
    const { session, user } = useAuth();
    const userData = user?.userData?.[0];
    const weekKey = getWeekKey();

    const [recapDismissed, setRecapDismissed] = useState(() => {
        try { return localStorage.getItem(weekKey) === 'true'; }
        catch { return false; }
    });

    const { data: recapData, isLoading: recapLoading } = useQuery({
        queryKey: ['weeklyRecap', session?.access_token],
        queryFn: () => getWeeklyRecap(session?.access_token),
        enabled: !!session?.access_token && !recapDismissed,
        staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 10,
        refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    });

    const { data: prompt, isLoading: promptLoading } = useQuery({
        queryKey: ['todaysPrompt'],
        queryFn: getTodaysPrompt,
        staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 30,
        refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    });

    const { data: responsesData } = useQuery({
        queryKey: ['promptResponses', prompt?.id],
        queryFn: () => getPromptResponses(prompt.id),
        enabled: !!prompt?.id,
        staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 5,
        refetchOnWindowFocus: false,
    });

    const { data: streakData } = useStreakData(userData?.id);

    const recap = recapData?.recap;
    const personal = recap?.personal || {};
    const group = recap?.group || {};
    const hasRecap = !recapDismissed && !recapLoading && recap && 
                     (personal.posts_written > 0 || group.total_posts > 0);
    const hasPrompt = !promptLoading && !!prompt;

    if (!hasRecap && !hasPrompt) return null;

    const handleDismissRecap = (e) => {
        e.stopPropagation();
        try { localStorage.setItem(weekKey, 'true'); } catch {}
        setRecapDismissed(true);
    };

    const today = new Date();
    const dateStr = today.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
        weekday: 'short', month: 'short', day: 'numeric' 
    });

    return (
        <AnimatePresence>
            <motion.div className="dashboard-briefing" ...>
                <div className="dashboard-briefing-header">
                    <div className="dashboard-header-left">
                        <div className="dashboard-accent-bar" />
                        <span className="dashboard-title">Today</span>
                        <span className="dashboard-date">{dateStr}</span>
                        {streakData?.current_streak > 0 && (
                            <StreakBadge count={streakData.current_streak} size={14} />
                        )}
                    </div>
                    {hasRecap && (
                        <button className="dashboard-dismiss-btn" onClick={handleDismissRecap}>
                            {/* X icon SVG */}
                        </button>
                    )}
                </div>
                <div className={`dashboard-briefing-grid ${!hasRecap ? 'prompt-only' : ''}`}>
                    <AnimatePresence mode="popLayout">
                        {hasRecap && (
                            <motion.div key="recap-section" exit={{ ... }}>
                                <RecapSection 
                                    personal={personal} 
                                    group={group} 
                                />
                            </motion.div>
                        )}
                        {hasRecap && hasPrompt && (
                            <motion.div key="divider" className="dashboard-divider" exit={{ ... }} />
                        )}
                    </AnimatePresence>
                    {hasPrompt && (
                        <PromptSection 
                            prompt={prompt}
                            responsesData={responsesData}
                            onWriteResponse={onWriteResponse}
                        />
                    )}
                </div>
            </motion.div>
        </AnimatePresence>
    );
};
```

